Title: _app.admin.observability._index page
Route file: web/routes/_app.admin.observability._index.tsx
Suggested path: /app/admin/observability

Role/Purpose
- Provide operational dashboard for monitoring service metrics, alerts, incidents, and log forwarders across the OMS platform.
- Enable operators to track SLO adherence, identify active incidents, and monitor alerting infrastructure health.

Primary UI Components
- `PageHeader` with title "Observability dashboard" and description.
- Optional error `Alert` when using fallback data (`source === "fallback"`).
- Summary cards showing: Metrics count, Open alerts count, Active incidents count, Forwarder issues count.
- `Tabs` component with four tabs: Metrics, Alerts, Incidents, Log Forwarders.
- Custom `Table` components in each tab showing relevant records with status badges and formatted values.
- Status badges with color coding: critical/high=rose/orange, warning=amber, healthy=emerald, degraded=amber, failed=rose.

Data Dependencies
- Loader calls four parallel API queries: `context.api.serviceMetric.findMany()`, `context.api.alert.findMany()`, `context.api.incident.findMany()`, `context.api.logForwarder.findMany()`.
- Metrics select: `id`, `serviceName`, `metric`, `currentValue`, `target`, `unit`, `direction`, `capturedAt` (first 25, sorted by capturedAt descending).
- Alerts select: `id`, `serviceName`, `type`, `severity`, `status`, `openedAt`, `acknowledgedAt`, `resolvedAt`, `runbookUrl`, `summary` (first 25, sorted by openedAt descending).
- Incidents select: `id`, `title`, `status`, `severity`, `startedAt`, `resolvedAt`, `summary`, `postmortemUrl` (first 25, sorted by startedAt descending).
- Forwarders select: `id`, `destination`, `provider`, `status`, `lastHeartbeatAt`, `notes` (first 25, sorted by destination ascending).
- If any model unavailable, returns `FALLBACK_DATA` with sample records and `source: "fallback"` + `error` message.
- Records normalized with guard functions to ensure type safety.

Actions & Side Effects
- Tab switching updates visible content (client-side).
- Summary metrics computed from loaded data (open alerts, active incidents, failing forwarders).
- Error alert displays when using fallback data.
